data.title: pWwew.net: WWE Summer Slam 1993
data.text:
WWF SUMMERSLAM 1993

The Palace at Auburn Hills

Auburn Hills, Michigan

August 30, 1993

Million Dollar Man Ted DiBiase vs. Razor Ramon

The turnbuckle pad was taken off and DiBiase hit his head on it. Razor then hit the Razor's Edge and got the pin.

The Steiner Brothers (WWF Tag Team Champions) vs. The Heavenly Bodies with Jim Cornette

The Heavenly Bodies missed a double team Moonsault, allowing a Frankensteiner from the Steiners and a double pin! The Steiner Brothers retain their titles.

Shawn Michaels (WWF Intercontinental Champion) with Diesel vs. Mr. Perfect

Diesel interfered in the match, throwing Perfect into the steel ring post, which got him counted out. Michaels retained his title.

1-2-3 Kid vs. Irwin R Shyster

IRS won in a quick match with the Write Off Clothesline.

Jerry Lawler comes out and says he is injured so he cannot wrestle against Bret Hart. He brings out Doink the Clown to wrestle Hart.

Doink the Clown vs. Bret "The Hitman" Hart

Bret Hart easily won with the Sharpshooter. As he is applying the move, Lawler comes into the ring and hits him with his crutch. WWF President Jack Tunney comes out and orders Lawler to wrestle in his match against Hart. . .

Bret "The Hitman" Hart vs. Jerry "The King" Lawler

King of the Ring Match

Bret Hart gets the win with the Sharpshooter, making Lawler tap out. But, Hart won't stop the hold, even after a team of referees come out and ask him to stop. The original referee reverses the decision and gives Lawler the win via disqualification. Lawler is declared the true "King of the Ring."

Marty Jannetty vs. Ludvig Borga

Borga gets the easy win with the Torture Rack Backbreaker.

Giant Gonzales with Harvey Wimpleman vs. The Undertaker

Rest in Peace Match

Paul Bearer makes his return to the WWF during the match, carrying a black wreath of flowers. Bearer gets possession of the urn again, giving strength to the Undertaker, allowing him to pin Gonzales after a Top Rope Clothesline. After the match, Giant Gonzales Chokeslams Wimpleman.

Tatanka & The Smoking Guns vs. Bam Bam Bigelow (with Luna Vachon) & The Headshrinkers

Tatanka pinned Samu with a roll up after his team missed a simultaneous top rope move.

Lex Luger vs. Yokozuna (WWF Heavyweight Champion)
